ebusgate
--------

ebusgate provides a communication interface too ebus equipped systems.

Usage:
  ebusgate [Options...]

Options:

-a | --address		ebus device address [FF]
-f | --foreground	run in foreground

-d | --device		ebus device (serial or network) [/dev/ttyUSB0]
-n | --nodevicecheck	disable test of local ebus device
   | --reopentime	max. time to open ebus device in 'sec' [60]

   | --arbitrationtime	waiting time for arbitration test 'us' [4400]
   | --receivetimeout	max. time for receiving of one sequence sign 'us' [4700]
   | --lockcounter	number of characters after a successful ebus access [5] (max: 25)
   | --lockretries	number of retries to lock ebus [2]

   | --active		handle broadcast and at me addressed messages

   | --store		store received messages

-p | --port		listen port [8888]
   | --local		listen only on localhost

   | --logfile		log file name [/var/log/ebusgate.log]
   | --loglevel		set logging level - off|error|warn|info|debug|trace [info]
   | --raw		toggle raw output

   | --pidfile		pid file name [/var/run/ebusgate.pid]

   | --dump		toggle raw dump
   | --dumpfile		dump file name [/tmp/ebus_dump.bin]
   | --dumpsize		max size for dump file in 'kB' [100]

   | --options
   | --version
-h | --help



tools (see local README)
------------------------

- ebusgatectl
- ebusgatefeed



For bugs and missing features use github issue system.

The author can be contacted at roland.jax@liwest.at.
